---
import Base from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---
<Base title="Open Source"><Fragment slot="header"><Header /></Fragment>

  <section class="relative pt-28 pb-16 overflow-hidden bg-subtle-grid" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#fafaf9 0%,#ffffff 30%,#ede9fe 100%)">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 relative"><div class="max-w-2xl"><p class="sl">Licensing</p><h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-heading font-bold text-stone-900 leading-tight mb-4">Open source</h1><p class="text-lg text-stone-600 max-w-xl">Everything we build is open by default. AGPL protects the commons, and dual-licensing keeps the model sustainable.</p></div></div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-20 border-t border-stone-100 reveal">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="prose space-y-8">
        <div><h2>Why AGPL</h2><p>The AGPL is the right licence for genomic infrastructure. It ensures that anyone who uses and modifies our software in a network context must contribute their changes back. This protects against large players taking community-built infrastructure closed without giving back — a problem MIT and BSD licences don't solve.</p><p>At the same time, AGPL lets the community freely use, modify, and redistribute every tool we build. No black boxes, no vendor lock-in, no surprise licensing costs.</p></div>
        <div><h2>Dual-licensing</h2><p>We offer commercial licences for organisations that need to integrate our software into closed products or proprietary platforms. This is how we fund ongoing maintenance, documentation, and development — not by gating features, but by providing a path for commercial use.</p><p>Contact hello@protomonlabs.org for dual-licensing enquiries.</p></div>
        <div><h2>Repositories</h2><p><strong>SV Browser</strong> — Open-source structural variant genome browser. AGPL. Paid support and custom deployment available.</p><p><strong>GA4GH Standards SDKs</strong> — Maintained reference implementations for approved GA4GH standards.</p><p><strong>Certification Infrastructure</strong> — Conformance verification tooling and badge system for standards adoption.</p><p><strong>Federated Browser</strong> — Distributed genome browser architecture for cross-institutional data sharing.</p></div>
        <div><h2>Contributing</h2><p>We welcome contributions. All repositories require a Contributor Licence Agreement (CLA) to protect the project's licensing model. See CONTRIBUTING.md in each repository for details.</p></div>
        <div><h2>Contact</h2><p>hello@protomonlabs.org</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

<Fragment slot="footer"><Footer /></Fragment></Base>